==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: oenanthylous
<hw>oe*nan"thyl*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of, pertaining to, or designating, an acid formerly supposed to be
the acid of oenanthylic ether, but now known to be a mixture of higher
acids, especially <altname>capric</altname> acid.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>oenocyan</ent>⟦br⟧
